> Im just wondering how important is charisma to an enchanter?  I made an Erudite enchanter as an alt and put 20 points in intelligence, 5 into charisma and 5 into agility.  Is this a mistake to do or should I put more into charisma?   <p>Brimhoff
55th Knight
<Harpers></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatterdmalion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatter DMalion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/21/01 12:43:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Here's my understanding.<br>
<br>
Both INT and CHA are important.  INT drives how much you can cast; while CHA drives your ability to charm and mez.  If I were to make an enchanter, I would put ALL my points into CHA.  Why?  It is far easier to get items with +INT than items with +CHA.  There are just more +INT items to be had.  Yes, an enchanter can buff their CHA with a spell, but my reasoning is based upon item selection.<br>
<br>
If you are want to go with the same race, which is CHA challenged, I'd recreate and put your points into CHA.  Put any left-over into INT.<br>
<br>
And remember, this is coming from someone who plays a bard.  Though I have looked into creating an enchanter.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaryinnmb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maryinn MB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/21/01 10:10:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.merryband.com/images/maryinn/maryinn.jpg width=150 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> The effects of Charisma are greatly exagerated.  I ran some mez tests at 100, 150 and 200 charisma one time.  The difference between 100 and 150 was noticable but not very large (5-10% difference) the different between 150 and 200 charisma was inconsequential (1%).<br>
<br>
The single most important thing in Everquest is your level vs the mobs level.  This goes for mezing, charming, nuking, meleeing, tanking, debuffing etc...  I would not worry about charisma after getting it to around 150 (also aim for int at 200 of course) and the people who buff it to 255 are foolish (GZ has admited a soft cap at 200).<br>
<br>
The most important stat for enchanters is hit points... <p>-<a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=998">Maryinn</a> 
&lt;<a href="http://www.watchers-brell.com">Watchers</a>&gt; (<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis">Brell Serilis</a>)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaryinnmb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maryinn MB</A> at: 5/21/01 10:20:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzyphbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyph Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tastes Like Chicken!</span><br>  Posts: 614<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/22/01 3:02:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> /agree maryinn<br>
<br>
I used to sacrifice certain equipment for 200int/cha then one day I had to mez to get back to our camp naked.. 132 cha and I didn't notice much at all.  Ever since then I hang at around 180 buffed.  Still trying to get 4k hps though and 900 AC<br>
<br>
Sit at 3k with cleric/shammie buffs and 804 ac.  One day I will make it.. I hope. <p><html>
