<br>
work on AC and HP, which is in my opinion, way more important than charisma.<br>
<br>
<br>
-<br>
Bulingit Ako <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueidolonfaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eidolon Faer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Dark Lord of Felwithe</span><br>  Posts: 497<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/24/01 6:28:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Sigpic.jpg height=233 width=103></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Charisma DOES seem to alter resist rates on Mez, and resist rate / duration on Charm.  But the effect, as Maryinn pointed out, is relatively minor.<br>
<br>
I am also not that impressed with the need for INT.  While I will crank my Int over 235 when practicing skills, I generally run Int 180-190 when combat-ready.<br>
<br>
My AC, however (with relatively non-uber gear) runs over 650 self-buffed, and hits 700 with a Cleric's help.  Even with Sebilis mobs, I notice a difference in the poundings I take when a fight gets hairy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Project4.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzyphbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyph Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tastes Like Chicken!</span><br>  Posts: 626<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/1/01 3:12:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Eidolon INT is what your mana pool is based off of.  200 is its max.  If you are running 180-190 int to sacrifice for cha..  I urge you to try a different approach.  Stay at 200+int and 180+ cha and life is good.   <p><html>
