</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazzimezzcaline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzi Mezzcaline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/5/01 11:01:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> THANK YOU for the question about something I actually tested.<br>
Maryinn, I have found the same to be true, with mez .. CHA doesn't really effect my abilities to mez.<br>
With Charm I'm failing to see the usefullness of Charisma all together. You would think the stat would be more useful than getting it to 100 and buying stuff at normal cost but I can sometimes charm w/ cha at 120 for the 13 minutes or I can wear my cha gear and buff up to 207 and charm for 6 seconds. <br>
<br>
I would still toss points into something other than INT .. INT is the easiest stat for INT casters to get up. <p><a href=http://www.etherealknighthood.com border=0><img src=http://home.kscable.com/ethereal/azzisig.gif></a><br><center>
"Hey, we all feel bad that when you were 12 your scoutmaster rubbed 
  your butt at the overnight jamboree, but dude, you're almost 30. It's 
  time to climb down off the cross, use the wood to build a bridge, and 
  get over it!"<br>
              -Chris Titus Wisdom<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubulingit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bulingit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/7/01 9:33:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Coming from an enchanter that charms on a regular basis, from my observation: Duration of charm is based on mainly the mob's Magic Resist. Try charming a Myconid Adept in sebilis without casting Tash and time the duration. When charm breaks, Tash, recharm and time the duration.<br>
<br>
If you get lucky and get a low level adept (lvl 52), your charm will last for a long time, but if you get a lvl 54 adept (borderline of charm level limit), then the charm duration would be minimal.<br>
<br>
Like I said, charisma is overrated. To be honest with you, I don't think any of your character's personal stats would affect any of the spell(s) impact on a mob.<br>
<br>
Charisma affects resist rate on mez and charm duration = BS<br>
Fear lasts longer with low charisma = BS<br>
Charisma affects bard songs on mobs = BS<br>
Higher Wisdom, the less resists you get with your spells = BS<br>
<br>
I don't think there's a code in EQ where it states that the spell you casted on a mob checks your stats and calculates it's resist roll value and duration affect on the target.  It's too complicated to write, especially with the amount of stats you have to calculate + the number of variable mobs with their own unique resist tag + any other variables that can easily challenge the integrity of the code.<br>
<br>
EQ is not that complicated, people just made it seem like it.<br>
<br>
-<br>
Bulingit Ako <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubulingit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bulingit</A> at: 6/7/01 9:42:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uymaeeldiezsomuch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YmaeelDiezsomuch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#CC9900>(7/8/01 12:49:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Wis/Int cap most say is 200 and +1 mana for every after<br>
<br>
If testing shows that having over 150 cha is more successful wouldn't that mean that your stats are calculated when you cast? If there is no calculating it wouldn't matter if a chanter had zero cha. Level is a big part of it but cha is figured in there somewhere, it wouldn't make sense for enc gear to have so much cha otherwise. I'm no enc but this seems somewhat common sense, if you don't think cha stat is calculated find a mob you can test on for yourself. <br>
<br>
<br>
Ymaeel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usinlesskraves.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinless Kraves</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#CC9900>(7/8/01 7:45:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> You need to put all into CHA I say, mainly because as an Erudite, you have a high INT to begin with.  Also INT items are much easier to come across, much less the price.  CHA items, as you may know are more expensive.  I do agree though, that you CHA doesnt affect your mezzes that well, although it is claimed that they do.  If you get the chance go back, and recreate the enchanter, an Erudite is a good choice, except for the certain special few who pick a GNOME!=P But thats my few cents worth, good luck with your chanter, send me a tell if you ever need any help, Id be happy to help any young enchanter!<br>
<br>
